description.narrative: Establish a partnership with CO/RO based on a mutually rewarding exchange of knowledge and experience. Global, regional and country offices have the tools to increase their capacity to effectively leverage the political power and reach of civil society organizations, religious leaders, parliamentarians to achieve the MDGs with equity. Increased capacity of countries to scale-up comprehensive Early Child Development (ECD) interventions for the most deprived and disadvantaged young children in regular and emergency settings, which contributes to Child Health, Child Poverty / Public Finance For Children, Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Early Childhood Development, Equitable Access To Quality Education, Field/Country Office Oversight, Management And Operations Support, Immunization, Operations Support To Programme Delivery, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Skills Development, Technical Excellence In Policy And Programmes. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Technical expertise and management support provided to all UNICEF work streams for the equitable achievement of the MDGs by 2015, realizing the rights of every child in humanitarian and development contexts
